## Group Skills for `<%= @namespace.full_path %>`

**Base URL:** <%= Gitlab.config.gitlab.url %>/api/v4

**Authentication:**

```bash
curl <%= Gitlab.config.gitlab.url %>/api/v4/... \
  -H "PRIVATE-TOKEN: YOUR_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN"
```

Group membership is inherited by every project under this group: a member's access level here applies to all projects in the group tree. Manage project-specific members from each project's own `-/members/skill.md`.

---

### Access Levels

| Level | Value |
|-------|-------|
| `guest` | Read-only access |
| `developer` | Can push to non-protected branches, create MRs |
| `maintainer` | Can manage members and settings |
| `owner` | Full control including deletion |

---

### Show the Group

```bash
curl "<%= Gitlab.config.gitlab.url %>/api/v4/groups/<%= @namespace.id %>" \
  -H "PRIVATE-TOKEN: YOUR_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN"
```

---

### Members

Manage members for this group. All requests require a personal access token in the `PRIVATE-TOKEN` header. Only group maintainers and owners may add, update, or remove members.

#### List Members

```bash
curl "<%= Gitlab.config.gitlab.url %>/api/v4/groups/<%= @namespace.id %>/members" \
  -H "PRIVATE-TOKEN: YOUR_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN"
```

**Response fields per member:**

| Field | Description |
|-------|-------------|
| `id` | User ID |
| `username` | Username |
| `name` | Display name |
| `state` | Account state (`active`, `blocked`) |
| `access_level` | Role in this group |
| `expires_at` | Membership expiry date (`YYYY-MM-DD`), or `null` if no expiry set (membership never expires) |
| `expired` | `true` if the membership has passed its expiry date; always `false` when `expires_at` is `null` |
| `web_url` | URL to the user's profile |

#### Get a Single Member

```bash
curl "<%= Gitlab.config.gitlab.url %>/api/v4/groups/<%= @namespace.id %>/members/:user_id" \
  -H "PRIVATE-TOKEN: YOUR_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN"
```

- `:user_id` — The numeric ID of the user
- Returns `404 Not Found` if the user is not a member of this group

#### Add a Member

Requires maintainer or owner access.

```bash
curl -X POST "<%= Gitlab.config.gitlab.url %>/api/v4/groups/<%= @namespace.id %>/members" \
  -H "PRIVATE-TOKEN: YOUR_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"user_id": 123, "access_level": "developer"}'
```

**Fields:**

- `user_id` (required) — Numeric ID of the user to add
- `access_level` (required) — One of `guest`, `developer`, `maintainer`, `owner`
- `expires_at` (optional) — Membership expiry date in `YYYY-MM-DD` format. Omit or pass `null` for no expiry

Returns `201 Created` with the member object on success.
Returns `404 Not Found` if the user does not exist.
Returns `422 Unprocessable Entity` if the user is already a member.

#### Update a Member's Access Level

Requires maintainer or owner access.

```bash
curl -X PUT "<%= Gitlab.config.gitlab.url %>/api/v4/groups/<%= @namespace.id %>/members/:user_id" \
  -H "PRIVATE-TOKEN: YOUR_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"access_level": "maintainer"}'
```

- `:user_id` — The numeric ID of the user
- `access_level` (required) — New role: `guest`, `developer`, `maintainer`, or `owner`
- `expires_at` (optional) — New expiry date in `YYYY-MM-DD` format, or `null` to clear expiry. Omit to leave the current value unchanged

Returns `200 OK` with the updated member object.
Returns `404 Not Found` if the user is not a member.

#### Remove a Member

Requires maintainer or owner access.

```bash
curl -X DELETE "<%= Gitlab.config.gitlab.url %>/api/v4/groups/<%= @namespace.id %>/members/:user_id" \
  -H "PRIVATE-TOKEN: YOUR_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN"
```

- `:user_id` — The numeric ID of the user to remove

Returns `204 No Content` on success.
Returns `404 Not Found` if the user is not a member.
Returns `403 Forbidden` when removing the last owner of the group.
